        "title": "array of DBObject with same keys each element",
        "body": "<p>I am trying to create an array of DBObject, all of the elements have the same key with different values. \nwhat is the problem with this implementation ? <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> DBObject[] Out = new BasicDBObject[2];\n\n out[0].put(\"VALUE\",\"1\");\n out[0].put(\"PROPERTY\",\"1\");\n\n out[1].put(\"VALUE\",\"2\");\n out[1].put(\"PROPERTY\",\"2\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "question_id": 47283872,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "mongodb",
            "dbobject"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "accepted_answer_id": 47284134,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 159
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/g2Ami.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 7611917,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5772498,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5772498/stefan",
                "reputation": 2415,
                "display_name": "Stefan"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1510657505,
            "creation_date": 1510657505,
            "body": "<p>First, <code>Out<\/code> and <code>out<\/code> are mixed up (use upper/lower case consistently)<\/p>\n\n<p>Second, you need to initialize the objects in the array before you can use them:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>DBObject[] out = new BasicDBObject[2];\n\nout[0] = new BasicDBObject();\nout[0].put(\"VALUE\",\"1\");\nout[0].put(\"PROPERTY\",\"1\");\n\nout[1] = new BasicDBObject();\nout[1].put(\"VALUE\",\"2\");\nout[1].put(\"PROPERTY\",\"2\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 47284134,
            "question_id": 47283872
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7f54a342abb0e3d15427e1ee5ae1e0f5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1683752,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1547430,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1547430/tharun",
                "reputation": 311,
                "display_name": "Tharun"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1510657824,
            "creation_date": 1510657824,
            "body": "<p>You are only creating array of references. You need to create objects for it before assigning values.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>DBObject[] Out = new BasicDBObject[2];\n\n// instantiating objects for the array\nfor(int i=0 ; i &lt; Out.length ; i++){\n    Out[i] = new BasicDBObject();\n}\n\nOut[0].put(\"VALUE\",\"1\");\nOut[0].put(\"PROPERTY\",\"1\");\nOut[1].put(\"VALUE\",\"2\");\nOut[1].put(\"PROPERTY\",\"2\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 47284264,
            "question_id": 47283872
        }
